Hi, Terry.

As Terry Guinn wrote to Dr. Math
On 08/23/2004 at 21:22:51 (Eastern Time),
>[Question]
>my freshman daughter wants me to help her with this problem:
>traffic light A turns Green every 4 minutes.
>traffic light B turns green every 5 minutes.
>If both lights just turned Green, how long will it be before both 
>lights turn green.
>
>[Difficulty]
>I don't see how to set up a solution.
>
>[Thoughts]
>I'm guessing it's a cross multiply, divide and conquer thing. working 
>it out by hand looks like a 20 or so page project and doesn't help 
>with future similiar problems.

You're looking for a time that is a multiple of both 4 minutes and 5
minutes, so that both lights will turn on at that time.

Ask your daughter if she has heard of the "least common multiple".
That should trigger some thoughts.

If you have any further questions, feel free to write back.


